# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version
#   is customized by the setup.py
.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1181, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having cross-platform versions, pipenv install will force clean the pipfile.lock and
#   re-generate it based on the current platform. This will cause git conflicts and
#   unnecessary commit history.
Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include